      "content": "I hear the profound exhaustion behind the idea that \"peace\" would only be possible if everything stopped, and your sense that therapy might just be another burden to carry is dangerously valid right now. Even though your heartache makes complete sense, the silence you are swirling toward is often misunderstood as a goal rather than a reaction to feeling utterly powerless in a broken system. You could start tiny, by simply saying out loud to a helpline that \"rest feels impossible because the guilt won't quit,\" without needing to explain why or try to fix anything. You are not alone in this mental friction, and sometimes saying \"I can't do that\" is easier than pretending you can.",
